I analyzed my own Instagram data… and the results were surprising 👀

Out of 540 people I follow, 108 don’t follow me back.

That’s ~20% 😅

So I built a full **Instagram Analytics Dashboard using Power BI** to understand what’s really going on behind the numbers.

📊 What I built:
• Followers vs Following analysis
• Not-following-back detection
• Engagement trends (likes vs comments)
• Story & activity tracking
• Monthly growth insights

📈 Key Insights:
• 84% follow-back rate
• Engagement peaked in Jan 2026
• Growth slowed after mid-2025
• 100+ accounts don’t follow back

🛠 Behind the scenes:
• Cleaned raw JSON data using Power Query
• Converted UNIX timestamps to readable dates
• Built a proper Date Table
• Created relationships (1:M model)
• Designed interactive visuals in Power BI

💡 Biggest learning:
Data is messy… but insights are powerful when you structure it right.

This project helped me understand:
→ Data cleaning
→ Data modeling
→ Dashboard storytelling

Would you unfollow people who don’t follow you back? 🤔

